  <Docs>
    <summary>
            Contains a set of parameters used to determine which activities are enabled for which listeners.
            An unspecified <see cref="P:Microsoft.Extensions.Diagnostics.Tracing.TracingRule.SourceName" /> matches all activity sources, an unspecified
            <see cref="P:Microsoft.Extensions.Diagnostics.Tracing.TracingRule.OperationName" /> matches all activities within the matching sources, and an unspecified
            <see cref="P:Microsoft.Extensions.Diagnostics.Tracing.TracingRule.ListenerName" /> matches all listeners.
            </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>The most specific rule that matches a given activity will be used. The priority of parameters is as follows:</para>
      <list type="bullet">
        <item>
          <description>ListenerName, an exact match. See <see cref="P:Microsoft.Extensions.Diagnostics.Tracing.ActivityListenerBuilder.Name" />.</description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>SourceName, either an exact match, the longest prefix match, or a wildcard pattern using a single <c>*</c>. See <see cref="P:System.Diagnostics.ActivitySource.Name" />.</description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>OperationName, an exact match. See <see cref="P:System.Diagnostics.Activity.OperationName" />.</description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>Scopes, where a more constrained scope is preferred over <c>Global | Local</c>.</description>
        </item>
      </list>
      <para>When multiple rules are equally specific, the rule added last takes precedence.</para>
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
